ENTRY            F1536   20251205   20260305   20260305       F106
SUBENT        F1536001   20251205   20260305   20260305       F106
BIB                 14         51
TITLE      Production cross sections of 233,232,230Pa and 231Th
           via 20.9 MeV proton irradiation of 232Th
AUTHOR     (Yu.E.Titarenko,A.A.Arkhipov,S.A.Balyuk,V.F.Batyaev,
           M.V.Batyaeva,V.D.Davidenko,V.M.Zhivun,Ya.O.Zaritskiy,
           A.A.Kovalishin,M.V.Kotelniy,A.S.Kirsanov,T.V.Kulevoy,
           I.V.Mednikov,B.A.Novikov,A.V.Orlov,K.V.Pavlov,
           V.S.Stolbunov,A.Yu.Titarenko,R.S.Tikhonov,
           M.N.Shlenskii,N.A.Kovalenko,S.E.Vinokurov,
           A.G.Kazakov,E.Yu.Khvorostinin,A.V.Ignatyuk)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSITE,4RUSFEI)
           (4RUSRUS) Vernadsky Institute of Geochemistry and
           Analytical Chemistry, Moscow
REFERENCE  (J,PAN,88,578,2025)
           #doi:10.1134/S1063778825601027
REL-REF    NUDAT2 Library (www.nndc.bnl.gov/nudat2). Decay data
           of Pa and Th isotopes were used by authors for
           cross-sections determination.
           (M,,Yu.E.Titarenko+,J,YK,,(2),60,2023)
           (M,,Yu.E.Titarenko+,R,INDC(CCP)-0453,2011) Analytical
           expressions for calculating the reaction rates and the
           mean (weighted average) values are presented.
FACILITY   (LINAC,4RUSITE) NS-21M facility.
METHOD     (ACTIV,GSPEC) Irradiation time was 1 hour and 1 min.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Two gamma-spectrometers were used. One was
           based on a coaxial HP Ge detector with an energy
           resolution of 1.7 keV at the 1332 keV gamma-line of
           60Co, and the other employed a planar HP Ge detector
           with a resolution of 0.50 keV at the 122 keV
           gamma-line of 57Co.
MONITOR    (29-CU-0(P,X)30-ZN-62,,SIG)
           (29-CU-0(P,X)30-ZN-63,,SIG)
SAMPLE     Experimental samples were punched from metallic
           thorium and copper foils using specially designed
           dies with diameters of 10.5 and 24 mm. The samples
           were assembled into sandwich-type stacks consisting
           of three layers: 232Th (diam. 10.5 mm) + natCu1
            (diam. 10.5 mm) + natCu2 (diam. 24 mm).
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Cross section error includes the
           uncertainty of the reaction rate definition only,
           which contains the statistical uncertainty of gamma
           peaks, the uncertainty of quantum yield, uncertainty
           of gamma quanta self-absorption in a sample material,
           uncertainty of absolute detection efficiency of gamma
           spectrometer.
ADD-RES    Production cross section of 230Pa at proton energy of
           200 MeV was obtained 3.50 +-0.22 mb.
           (COMP) Comparison with the results of PHITS-3.31 code
           simulations and data of the TENDLE-2023 library.
STATUS     (TABLE,,Yu.E.Titarenko+,J,PAN,88,578,2025) Table 1
           (APRVD) Entry was approved by Dr. Yu.E. Titarenko.
HISTORY    (20251205C)
ENDBIB              51
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV
       20.9
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           58
SUBENT        F1536002   20251205   20260305   20260305       F106
BIB                  5         11
REACTION   (90-TH-232(P,X)91-PA-233,,SIG)
CORRECTION Not corrected for 232Th(n,gamma)233Th(beta-)233Pa
           reaction.
DECAY-DATA (91-PA-233,26.975D,DG,311.90,0.385)
           Error of gamma intensity value is 0.004.
ANALYSIS   The value of the reaction rate divided by proton flux
           density was used to obtain the cross section value.
COMMENT    *By author* The value of the reaction rate and
           uncertainty obtained, in units 1/sec:
           Egamma, keV Reaction rate Uncertainty
           311.90      1.4749E-16    2.8260E-18
ENDBIB              11
